# book.chapter assignments
# (empty - populate as modules are added)# System Requirements
This collection captures user requirements and use cases.
Each module (book) contains its requirements organized by component (chapter).UC-1: System Initialization
Actor: Developer
Precondition: Empty workspace
Flow:
1. Developer creates a new 6D UML phext document
2. System populates Meta collection with defaults
3. System presents the requirement entry point
Postcondition: Living document ready for development# System Design
This collection captures architecture and UML diagrams.
Diagrams here are live entry points into the source (collection 4),
tests (collection 5), and documentation (collection 7).@startuml 6D-UML-Core
class PhextDocument {
  +content: String
  +fetch(coord: Coordinate): String
  +insert(coord: Coordinate, content: String)
  +walk_collection(addr_5d: Address5D): Stack
}

class Address5D {
  +volume: usize
  +book: usize
  +chapter: usize
  +section: usize
  +scroll: usize
  +to_coordinate(collection: usize): Coordinate
}

class ArtifactStack {
  +address: Address5D
  +layers: Vec<(usize, String)>
  +push(collection: usize, content: String)
  +peek(collection: usize): String
  +walk(): Iterator<(usize, String)>
}

class CollectionMap {
  +assignments: HashMap<usize, String>
  +phase(collection: usize): String
  +update(collection: usize, name: String)
}

PhextDocument --> Address5D
PhextDocument --> ArtifactStack
PhextDocument --> CollectionMap
@enduml# Source Code
Implementation artifacts live here.
Each unit at a 5D address corresponds to its requirement (collection 2)
and design (collection 3) at the same address.# Tests
Unit and integration tests.
Test addresses mirror the source they validate.# Regressions
Regression test suites tracking known issues and their fixes.# Documentation
Developer and user documentation.
Each artifact's docs live at the same 5D address as its source.# Whitepapers
Technical papers and research supporting design decisions.# Training
Onboarding and training materials for new team members.